WEBVTT

00:00.117 --> 00:01.758
Previously on
<i>Sanctuary...</i>

00:01.783 --> 00:04.001
It's amazing. I always
thought I was alone.

00:05.097 --> 00:06.378
Now I know it's not true.

00:07.615 --> 00:09.516
- I want you to stay.
- I want you to come with me--

00:09.518 --> 00:11.684
I grew up in an
institution for abnormals.

00:11.686 --> 00:13.820
The Sanctuary's more than that.
It's a family.

00:13.822 --> 00:15.955
The abnormals are
moving in formation.

00:15.957 --> 00:17.223
Someone, or something

00:17.225 --> 00:19.153
is in complete control
of these beings.

00:19.155 --> 00:20.744
What the hell
happened to you?

00:20.746 --> 00:23.217
You were out of
communication for hours.

00:23.219 --> 00:25.816
More like years, actually.

00:25.818 --> 00:26.817
Years?

00:26.819 --> 00:29.115
113, to be precise.

00:31.285 --> 00:32.949
I went through the files
on Addison's team.

00:32.951 --> 00:34.150
A lot of Ivy league
educations,

00:34.152 --> 00:35.285
state department
resumes,

00:35.287 --> 00:36.761
no marriages or kids.

00:36.763 --> 00:38.630
"Orphans preferred,"
lovely.

00:38.632 --> 00:42.075
What do we know about
this Addison fellow himself?

00:42.077 --> 00:44.046
He's the U.N. Security
Council's top troubleshooter.

00:44.048 --> 00:45.683
Harvard law,

00:45.685 --> 00:47.220
Brookings Institute,
The Hague.

00:47.222 --> 00:48.557
He's advised world leaders
on everything

00:48.559 --> 00:49.695
from Iraq, to Libya,

00:49.697 --> 00:51.330
to the B.P. Oil spill
in the Gulf.

00:51.332 --> 00:53.198
Wow, now he's here
to deal with us.

00:53.200 --> 00:54.333
If he wasn't
such a pit bull,

00:54.335 --> 00:55.736
I'd be flattered.

00:55.738 --> 00:56.570
Hmm.

00:58.140 --> 00:59.774
Terminal farm's
up and running

00:59.776 --> 01:00.943
in the research lab.

01:00.945 --> 01:02.412
Are you sure you want me
to give these guys

01:02.414 --> 01:04.083
complete access
to our current protocols?

01:04.084 --> 01:05.417
Bunch of strangers
poking around,

01:05.419 --> 01:06.252
I don't like it.

01:06.254 --> 01:07.623
Nobody does,

01:07.625 --> 01:08.890
but it's not like
we have a choice.

01:08.892 --> 01:10.025
What about
the "tea with Magnus,

01:10.027 --> 01:11.060
photo op with
a mermaid" option?

01:11.062 --> 01:11.928
That ain't gonna fly
this time.

01:11.930 --> 01:13.263
Everything's changed

01:13.265 --> 01:14.732
since the Calderas
to Hollow Earth were breached.

01:14.734 --> 01:16.033
High-level people
need reassurance

01:16.035 --> 01:18.673
that the situation
is under control.

01:18.675 --> 01:20.776
You've secured
the research database?

01:20.778 --> 01:22.178
Done.

01:22.180 --> 01:23.113
Current security
and user activity

01:23.115 --> 01:24.315
are open access.

01:24.317 --> 01:25.383
The rest is behind
an invisible firewall.

01:25.385 --> 01:27.686
And I'll be
monitoring their traffic

01:27.688 --> 01:28.755
full time,

01:28.757 --> 01:29.890
so we'll know right away

01:29.892 --> 01:31.158
if they try anything
off the hook.

01:31.160 --> 01:33.026
All secure
on the residential levels?

01:33.028 --> 01:34.094
No stragglers?

01:34.096 --> 01:35.262
Tight as a drum.

01:35.264 --> 01:36.363
Total lockdown
in 40 minutes.

01:36.365 --> 01:38.333
Good job, everyone.

01:38.335 --> 01:42.003
Right, one more walkthrough,
and we'll reconvene here at--

01:43.639 --> 01:45.806
What, an hour
ahead of schedule?

01:45.808 --> 01:48.108
No, there's no way.
Gate defenses are up.

01:48.110 --> 01:49.810
There is no way he just
walked to the front door.

01:49.812 --> 01:51.144
Yeah, see?

01:51.146 --> 01:53.046
Gate was opened
with an approved code.

01:53.048 --> 01:54.214
Mine...

01:55.817 --> 01:57.652
Well, who'd you give it to?

01:57.654 --> 01:59.054
No one.

02:00.691 --> 02:02.091
To the best of my knowledge.

